# .trivyignore

# CVE-2026-8376: Perl heap buffer overflow when compiling regex with a
# repeated fixed string -- only affects 32-bit Perl builds. Our base image
# (python:3.12-slim-bookworm) is amd64/64-bit; the overflow condition cannot
# trigger on a 64-bit build. Architecture-inapplicable.
CVE-2026-8376

# CVE-2026-42496: Archive::Tar (perl-archive-tar) path traversal via crafted
# symlinks during extraction (_make_special_file does not validate symlink
# targets). App contains no Perl invocation and no archive/tar extraction
# of any kind -- inherited from base image only, code path unreachable.
CVE-2026-42496

# Base image CVEs pending upstream fix -- tracked in issue #X
CVE-2026-12087
CVE-2026-48959
CVE-2026-48962

# False positive: Debian's zlib1g package does not compile contrib/minizip,
# so the vulnerable zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 code path doesn't exist in the
# installed binary. Confirmed via Debian security tracker (status: ignored)
# and aquasecurity/trivy#6722.
CVE-2023-45853

# Requires attacker-controlled arbitrary SQL execution (large ORDER BY
# expression list). App (app/main.py) contains no database access, no SQL,
# and no sqlite3 usage of any kind -- three static FastAPI routes only.
# Vulnerable code path is unreachable.
CVE-2025-7458
